  <description type="morphology">Annuals, 1–20 cm; herbage lemon-scented. Leaves (crowded at stems tips) 10–45 × 1–3 mm, bases of distal blades notably expanded. Peduncles mostly 1–10 mm (often wholly or partially concealed by bases of subtending leaves). Phyllaries linear, 2.5–5.5 mm, widths ± uniform throughout, each with 1–2 subterminal oil-glands 0.2–0.5 mm plus smaller, submarginal oil-glands. Cypselae 2.5–4 mm; pappi usually coroniform, 0.1–0.3 mm (plus 1–7 awns or bristles in some Texas populations). 2n = 24 (as P. cf. texana).</description>
